## Context
Reviewer 1 §1 + editor E2. The paper attributes climate-finance construction to
"economists," but named actors (Corfee-Morlot, Jachnik, Caruso, DAC
statisticians) are policy professionals. Table 2 venues are climate/energy
policy journals — no AER/QJE/JPE/JEEM. Either reframe as diffusion of economic
*rationality* (cost-benefit, efficiency, market-failure) into institutional
practice, or supply evidence of individual economists' intellectual role.

## Actions
1. Decide the framing (rationality-diffusion vs individual-economists) — author call; default to rationality-diffusion, which the corpus supports.
2. Rewrite the intro claim (p17 "it was economists in international organisations who built the measurement instruments") accordingly.
3. Add a paragraph addressing the economics-journal absence (Table 2) explicitly: real disciplinary composition vs source-selection effect (ties to 0136 corpus-boundary justification).
4. Cite Golka (2024) on epistemic authority exercised through financial institutions, not solely economists (→ 0143).

## Test
- Manuscript asserts the chosen framing consistently; grep for "economists" attributions cross-checked against the framing.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Central claim reframed and internally consistent
- [ ] Econ-journal absence addressed in text
- [ ] Golka (2024) cited
